The paper deals with the problem of rank-1 L1-norm-based TUCKER2 decomposition of 3-way tensors, which involves optimization and numerical analysis. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
